sec.p:
A wave is a perturbation that propagates through space and time, which is usually accompanied by energy transference. Despite the common knowledge that a wave should be “wavy”, it is not necessary for the wave signal to be periodic. The main property of a wave is its propagation that is characterised by its phase and group speeds. More rigorously, a wave is a signal that, in the simplest, one-dimensional case, is described by the general solution to the wave equation, f(z−Ct)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
