				\begin{document}$f$\end{document} that describes the wave shape is an arbitrary, sufficiently smooth function that is determined by the excitation. In particular, it may be periodic, e.g. harmonic, or aperiodic, e.g. Gaussian.

In a more general case the function f\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
