In dispersive media or systems, signals with different frequencies have different phase and group speeds, for example a fast magnetoacoustic wave propagating within a system with a field-aligned inhomogeneity. In this case, different spectral components that are the results of the Fourier decomposition of the function f\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
