				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\mathbf{B}_{\mathrm{buoyant}}$\end{document} yield a range of associated periodicities of 105–212.5 s for 2.6×103G≤Bbuoyant≤3.9×103G\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$2.6 \times 10^{3}~\mbox{G} \le \mathbf{B}_{\mathrm{buoyant}} \le 3.9 \times 10^{3}~\mbox{G}$\end{document}, where the stronger the initial flux tube strength, the longer the period of oscillation. Note that if the flux tube strength is too low (for McLaughlin et al. 2012a, this was Bbuoyant<2.6×103G\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
