				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$E_{x}$\end{document} will be a general feature and can be found in both the kinetic and non-kinetic scales, although the shape of the profile is different from that in Tajima et al. (1987). In addition to this, the anharmonicity of the oscillations is also a distinct feature of the nonlinear large amplitude regime of the coalescence. The anharmonicity is clearly seen only in the nonlinear regime. The theory of Tajima et al. (1987) is constructed under the assumption that the gas pressure can be ignored during the implosion, but the gas pressure significantly increases at the center of the current sheet and produces two MHD fast-mode shocks (Forbes 1982; Takeshige et al. 2015).

