This mechanism may also easily explain drifts of the QPP periods, that are often observed in flares. For example, Dennis et al. (2017) detected high-quality oscillations of the time derivative of the soft X-ray emission of the decay phase of a flare, with the period gradually increasing from 25 s to 100 s. If the detected QPPs are produced by the alternate current, a gradual decrease in the equilibrium current I0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
